Package ca.projectTOMi.tomi.model

Provides classes for holding data that can be persisted to the database.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Client
    A model class for storing information related to the Client.
    Entry
    An entry is one weeks' worth of work on a specific component.
    Expense
    An Expense is anything other than a user's billable hours that is being charged towards a Project's budget.
    Project
    A Project represents a project that either needs to be completed, or has been completed (dependent on it's active status.) Projects are worked on by specific UserAccount lead by a project manager.
    Task
    A Task represents a deliverable for the client.
    Team
    A Team represents a group of Accounts whom work under the same team lead.
    Timesheet
    Class representing a single timesheet for a user for a specific week.
    UnitType
    A Unit Type is used to distinguish between types of units.
    UserAccount
    A model class that contains information about accounts in the TOMi system.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Status
    Represents the submission status of a timesheet or an entry.

Package ca.projectTOMi.tomi.model Description
